       ('1854b18a-b49e-4d67-9d48-3e481139b867', '2026-05-03 19:53:11.040135+00', '2026-05-03 19:53:11.040135+00', false,
        '9000', 'Kimi to Anime ga Mitai', null, 'BABYMETAL x Kiba of Akiba ', '2012-03-07', 'R',
        'BABYMETAL x Kiba of Akiba', '2012', '', null, null, null, '#### ***Fandom***
**Kimi to Anime ga Mitai - Answer for Animation with You** is the bonus song from BABYMETALs joint single *BABYMETAL x Kiba of Akiba*.
This BABYMETAL song is a cover of the Kiba of Akiba song Animation With You, released from them in 2011.
The lyrics have been changed as to represent a girls point of view.
#### ***Genius.com***
*Babymetal × Kiba of Akiba* (BABYMETAL×キバオブアキバ) is a joint single by the bands Babymetal and Kiba of Akiba. The single was first released in Japan on March 7, 2012 to promote the album Sakura Gakuin 2011 Nendo: Friends.
#### ***natalie.mu***
The new album will be released as a split album with Kiba of Akiba, a "nerdy death pop band" from Kyoto that mixes screamo and otaku culture.
#### ***Wikipedia***
Nakamoto stated that the song was the first time she had heard metal death growls, though the growls were ultimately left to the other two members for the cover.
Unlike the original song, the chorus contains background vocals from Mizuno and Kikuchi. The latter called the song one of the band''s beloved, thanking Kiba of Akiba for the introduction.

The single artwork depicts a fox who has grown fangs (the former is motif for Babymetal, while the latter is a motif for Kiba of Akiba) holding up a kitsune sign with Akihabara in the background.',
        null, null, null),
