       ('450d14b5-d6f3-43d7-b6fb-c4f6b6ed42b0', '2026-05-03 19:53:11.040135+00', '2026-05-03 19:53:11.040135+00', false,
        '9810', 'Kasuka na Hana', null, 'Tatsuya Kitani (feat. BABYMETAL)', '2025-12-20', 'R', 'Kasuka na Hana', '2026',
        '', null, null, null, '#### Not fully released. Just as short trailer available.
***MANTANWEB***
It has been announced that singer-songwriter Tatsuya Kitani and metal dance unit BABYMETAL will be performing the opening theme "Kasuka na Hana" for the second season of the TV anime "Hell''s Paradise: Jigokuraku". Kitani wrote the lyrics and composed the song, which he will sing together with BABYMETAL.

**Kitani’s comment**:
"*A flower is someone who has the strength to take root in the soil and the weakness to sway in the wind, and who is unfazed by anything and exists as it should. A person who accepts doubt and realizes himself as he lives with doubt. This way of being, which embodies the way uncertainty and uncertainty blooms, is modest yet dignified, and is an ideal form. I wrote a song filled with my admiration for such a ''faint flower''.*"

**BABYMETAL’s comments**:
"*We usually collaborate with metal bands, but we''re really happy that our collaboration with Tatsuya Kitani has brought out a new side of BABYMETAL. When we heard this song, we felt like the gracefully blooming flower taught us the preciousness and beauty of "our existence." We hope that everyone can find a small happiness that they want to protect, like a faint flower.*"
', null, null, null),
